The paper deals with few-shot classification, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes an ensemble method to improve the performance of few-shot classification models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses deep neural networks to solve the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of meta-learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, indicating that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
